AGI - Pope Francis " decided to convene a Consistory > which will cover the next canonizations". It is read in the Bulletin of the press room of the Holy See in which it refers that in the audience yesterday, to the Policlinico Gemelli, granted to the Secretary of State, Cardinal Pietro Parolin and the Replacement for General Affairs, Monsignor Edgar Pena Parra, the Pontiff authorized the Dicastery of the Causes of Saints> to promulgate decrees regarding 5 servants of God and two Blesseds.
For these last two Blesseds, Francis decided to call a Consistory where the dates of the canonizations will be said. &nbsp;
<h2>Papa: for better comparison with migrants
&nbsp;"It would be a good Lenten exercise to confront the concrete reality of some migrant or pilgrim and let it involve us, in order to find out what God asks us to be better travelers towards the Father's house. This is a good 'examination' &nbsp; for the traveller". Pope Francis writes in the Message for Lent > on the theme "let us take together in hope".
<br The Pontiff wants to offer some reflections on the theme of the Message. "The motto of the Jubilee 'Pellegrins of Hope' &nbsp;> suggests the long journey of the people of Israel towards the promised land, narrated in the book of Exodus: the difficult journey <br> from slavery to freedom, desired and guided by the Lord, who loves his people and always is faithful to him". "And we cannot remember the biblical exodus without thinking - it emphasizes - to many brothers and sisters who today flee from situations of misery and violence and go in search of a better life for themselves and their loved ones. Here comes a first call to conversion, because we are all pilgrims in life, but everyone can ask themselves: how do I let myself challenge this condition? Am I really on the road or rather paralyzed, static, with fear and lack of hope, or in my comfort zone? Looking for paths of liberation from situations of sin and lack of dignity? ".
