AGI -&nbsp;The Competition and Market Authority has initiated an investigation against Atac for possible incorrect commercial practice. The investigation covers the quality and quantity of services provided in the three-year period 2021-2023 with respect to the provisions of the service contract with the Municipality of Rome > and provided to consumers also through the Charter of Quality of Public Transport Services.
In particular, we read in a note "Atac would have systematically disregarded the objectives relating to the regularity of the service > of surface transport and metro transport, to the safety offices of the metro stations, to the operation of lifts, lifts and stairs/mobile maps, > and to the lighting of the metro stations". &nbsp;
In view of the alleged failure to achieve these objectives, Atac "would not seem to have taken appropriate corrective measures to fill the repeated deficiencies, nor adjustment measures and/or partial reimbursement of the charges applied, in view of the potential inconveniences to consumers" concludes the Antitrust note. Yesterday the officials of the Authority carried out an inspection at the headquarters of the company Atac S.p.A. with the help of the Special Antitrust Nucleus of the Guardia di Finanza.&nbsp;>
<h2> From Atac maximum collaboration
"ATAC as always intends to confirm complete availability and openness >&nbsp; in relation to the request for information received by the Authority of the guarantor of competition and market, in form and content. He writes the company in a note.&nbsp;<br> <br> "The entire management body immediately became available in providing all the required information and in specifying the operating methods of the typical processes of service delivery and its consumption. Operations took place in a climate of absolute and total collaboration and transparency. - continues -&nbsp; On the merits, ATAC remembers that the company, led by its management, is engaged in an important work of renewal > of assets and business procedures, which has produced visible improvements in all management, although under conditions influenced by the numerous yards prepared in preparation for the Jubilee, >consulting gradually to recover the past shortcomings determined by a prolonged deficit of investments of the previous administrations". &nbsp;
<h2>Codacons, fundamental instructor to study rivalry
"In recent years we have presented a burst of complaints about the chronic disservices of the local transport of Rome, from the mobile stairs of the metro constantly out of use at stations that flood in case of rain, > from the buses that go on fire to the frequent interruptions of the metropolitan service. Situations that give an obvious harm to users who, in the face of the payment of tickets and subscriptions, would receive a service not in accordance with the standards" > writes the Codacons in a commentary note of the investigation.&nbsp;
"The Antitrust investigation is of fundamental importance because, if irregularities and lack of respect for the service contract and obligations assumed through the Charter of Quality of Public Transport Services, it will be possible to study actions of rivalry on behalf of users > who have paid Atac tickets and subscriptions. > In this sense the Codacons will intervene in the procedure of the Antitrust as a damaged subject, and will open on its site a page where citizens will be able to report problems and disservices related to public transport > managed by Atac".&nbsp;
<h2> Consumer union,excellent training
The Antitrust investigation against Atac for possible unfair commercial practice, for disregarding the objectives set out in the service contract with the Municipality of Rome is "a good precedent" >: Massimiliano Dona, president of the National Consumer Union.
"Finally, an investigation is open against those who offer a bad public transport service, insufficient, inadequate, unrespectful of the users and quality commitments contained in the Service Charter," says Dona.
